title: Google\Cloud\Filestore\V1\NetworkConfig
name: NetworkConfig
description:
Network configuration for the instance.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.filestore.v1.NetworkConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.network
params.description: The name of the Google Compute Engine VPC network to which the instance is connected.

params.name: data.modes
params.description: Internet protocol versions for which the instance has IP addresses assigned. For this version, only MODE_IPV4 is supported.

params.name: data.reserved_ip_range
params.description: A /29 CIDR block in one of the internal IP address ranges that identifies the range of IP addresses reserved for this instance. For example, 10.0.0.0/29 or 192.168.0.0/29. The range you specify can't overlap with either existing subnets or assigned IP address ranges for other Cloud Filestore instances in the selected VPC network.
